main event: Three white, round objects were observed climbing at a high speed in Coral Gables, Florida.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 3 seconds., The objects were seen in a formation, possibly indicative of breaking apart., They reflected light and were estimated to be 30 degrees in size and 20 degrees apart., There was no report of disappearance of the objects., The conclusion of the report indicated insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: military observer, possibly a reliable commercial pilot
